main event: A civilian photographer observed two white spots over New York, N.Y. on 15 February 1955.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 1.5 minutes,The objects appeared to be rotating or gyrating during the film development process,There was no previous sighting reported for these objects,The conclusions suggest they could be balloons or astronomical phenomena,The report indicates that multiple conclusions were drawn regarding the nature of the objects.
sighted object: two white spots with darker bands
